		<!-- message -->
		<div>Blacksnow didn't legitimitely level characters or acquire items.  In fact, selling characters is a minor part of their "business plan".  Their actual business revolves around selling duped items and the in game cash that comes from selling those duped items to vendors.  They don't hack the client, but they use errors in the code that allow exploits.  You will notice that they were primarily AO and now DAoC driven, correct?  That's because Verant is a much more solid bit of programming and takes the sanctity of earning your way very seriously.<br />
<br />
Don't let their "Gamer's Bill Of Rights" fool you. It's just a smokescreen Blacksnow created to try to build sympathy amongst the gaming community so that they could continue their rampant exploitation and money laundering scams.  They don't give a rat's ass about the gamer. All they care about is that people continue to pay them for items and cash.<br />
<br />
AVault, in the linked post above,  has couched this argument as strictly an issue from the perspective of Joe Gamer who spends 6 months leveling his character, quits the game and makes a few bucks by ebaying. I don't know why they've chosen to put up such a false presentation of the facts.  Perhaps they know people at Blacksnow.<br />
<br />
The *real* story of what this is all about is here<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/15/442.php" target="_blank">http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/15/442.php</a><br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/15/446.php" target="_blank">http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/15/446.php</a><br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/16/449.php" target="_blank">http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/16/449.php</a><br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/18/454.php" target="_blank">http://www.unknownplayer.com/archive/02/03/18/454.php</a><br />
<br />
The best and most insightful information of all is in the icq logs provided by Blacksnow's Director of Sales, Lee Caldwell to Unknownplayer.  Why they would want to post their own logs which would reveal them as the criminals that they are is beyond me.  All I can think of is that Caldwell must think that Showing Young to be agreeing to work some back room deals makes Funcom look guilty. He must *still* not realize that he was played and played hard.  As soon as Funcom had the info they needed, they shut Caldwell and Blacksnow down fast and pulled back all of the concessions they had made as part of "the deal".<br />
<br />
The logs between Caldwell and Adam Young, Lead Database Admin for Funcom.  How Young finesses Caldwell into giving up his exploits is pure, undercover genius. <br />
<br />
Here they are.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.unknownplayer.com/images/blacksnow/icqlogs.html" target="_blank">http://www.unknownplayer.com/images...ow/icqlogs.html</a><br />
<br />
It's back alley extortion and con artistry at it's finest.  It's pure, simply, out of control greed and a complete disregard for the property of others OR the MMORPG community.  We are simply sheep for them to fleece.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
