It would appear likely that some of these scumbag dinkweeds (BlackSnow) had kept their accounts with the gaming news nets to get the "free ticket" or at least a better chance at getting into future closed betas.<br />
<br />
As for the topic at large, it is phenomenal how sick the human condition is. I always felt ripping MP3's off the net (as a musician) was among the most dishonorable things one could do. My stance has liberated on that somewhat ...<br />
<br />
... then later, after becoming an EQ victim, the topic of Ebayed characters always gave me a queasy feeling .. I can <i>almost</i> see the argument that a player is selling his "time" .. but it still doesn't <i>feel</i> right to me.<br />
<br />
This whole scheme of BlackSnow is without a doubt, however, far above and beyond any "casual ebay selling of my old character". It is a business model based on the outright exploitation of intellectual data, and to further insult the artist's (gamemaker's) work, they turn around and sell it for ridiculous amounts of money. Then they have the frelling <b>nerve</b> to sue the companies that banned thier accounts?!<br />
<br />
If I ever walked past these douchebags on the street I would find myself hard pressed not to show them some "leet exploits"<br />
