		<!-- message -->
		<div>Actually, that happens.  I was an indirect acquaintance of a guy who owned a cyber cafe/lan party business.  He had about 30 workstations set up and he would pay kids to come in and level characters and obtain items.   They were paid $10 an hour and were given their own private account that he paid for. Then he would ebay the items and the characters.  Totally lame.  However, there wasn't an exploit or hack involved. These were real people, leveling legitimately. Well, of course they were abusing quests for exp and whatever, but nothing like duping items or leveling to 50 in 12 minutes like Blacksnow did.<br />
<br />
The bottom line here is that people need to understand that if it is profitable for someone to sell in game stuff for real money, then they will do whatever is necessary to maximize their profitability. They don't care a bit about gamers or the game.  Those things/people are just there to serve them.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
